snippet.textDisplay:
Just listened again. Kihyun really has gotten overbearing in the last 8 months. He doesn't know when to back off and let the other guys come to the fore. Shownu is singing his heart off ‚Äî and sounds glorious ‚Äî but there's Kihyun blasting his part into the microphone instead of playing counterpoint/descant the way he's meant to. Same at the end. He's oversinging his adlibs and as a result, we don't get to hear Minhyuk do that really nice, simple bit at the end. It would have been a great time for the audience to sing along with him, too, as was originally intended in the recorded version.

I will note that they did clean up some of the backing vocals.

snippet.textDisplay: The synergy Kihyun has with Minhyuk and Shownu when singing really depicts the lyrics Changkyun wrote. There's an urgency and a seductive pull to it. Hyungwon's lines really set the mood and Jooheon and I.M's rap bring the song to another level. I'm so glad this song won out of the ones listed for this program because it's the opposite of their title songs and shows that they're versatile (and it's member produced). They are able to really showcase their usually overlooked vocal talent as a group since their Korean comebacks are consistently aggressive, high-energy, and powerful.
